Package com.sun.tools.visualvm.application.type

Package with basic ApplicationType(s).

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApplicationType
    This class is used to indetify different type of Java applications.
    ApplicationTypeFactory
    The ApplicationTypeFactory class is a factory class for getting the ApplicationType representation for the Application.
    DefaultApplicationType
    Default application type, which returns main class name as application name and uses generic Java icon as application icon.
    EclipseApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents Eclipse application.
    EclipseApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes Eclipse application.
    IntellijApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents IntelliJ Platform application.
    IntellijApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes application based IntelliJ Platform.
    JavaPluginApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represent Java-Plugin.
    JavaPluginApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes Java-Plugin application
    JavaWebStartApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represent Java Web Start application.
    JavaWebStartApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes Java Web Start Application
    JDeveloperApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents JDeveloper IDE application.
    JDeveloperApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes JDeveloper 11g and 10g.
    MainClassApplicationType
    ApplicationType which has custom name and icon.
    MainClassApplicationTypeFactory
    This application type factory recognizes some well-known Java application based on their main class name.
    MavenApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents Apache Maven application.
    MavenApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes Apache Maven.
    NetBeans3xApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents NetBeans 3.x application
    NetBeansApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents NetBeans application from version 4.0.
    NetBeansApplicationTypeFactory
    Factory which recognizes NetBeans IDE, NetBeans Platform based application and VisualVM itself
    NetBeansBasedApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents application based on NetBeans Platform.
    VisualVMApplicationType
    This ApplicationType represents VisualVM.
